{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Bunda People |population = |region1 = [[Idiofa Territory]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] |pop1 = |ref1 = |region2 = |pop2 = |ref2 = |region3 = |pop3 = |ref3 = |languages = [[Mpuono language]] |religions = |related = |footnotes = }} The '''Bunda people''' or (also ''Ambuun'', ''Mbuun'') in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] are an ethnic group that mostly live in [[Idiofa Territory]], [[Kwilu District]] of [[Bandundu Province]]. They speak the [[Mpuono language]], spoken by an estimated 165,000 people as of 1972.{{sfn|Ethnologue}}
==Location== The Belgian colonial administration originally gave Idiofa Territory the name of "Babunda Territory" after the Bunda people, who formed the majority of the population.{{sfn|Schwetz|1924|p=73}} They are still the most important group in the center of Idiofa territory.{{sfn|Plan stratégique}} The Bunda are the majority of the population of the administrative center of [[Idiofa]].{{sfn|Munzumi|2006|p=20}} There are also Bunda populations in [[Bulungu Territory]] and [[Gungu Territory]].{{sfn|RDC Ministère du Plan|2005}}
==Economy== The Bundu territory has a tropical climate with alternating dry and rainy seasons. The region has abundant water resources, the most important rivers being the [[Lubwe River|Lubwe]], [[Loange River|Loange]], [[Kamtsha River|Kamtsha]] and the [[Piopio River|Piopio]]. Precipitation in the rainy season is so intense that it is a major obstacle to farming and a time when food may be scarce. Hunting and fishing are individual activities during this period. Food is abundant in the dry season, the main season for communal hunting and fishing.{{sfn|Munzumi|2006|p=20}}
