==Notable Tausūgs==
[[File:Sitti 9 (2755513411).jpg|thumb|[[Sitti|Sitti Navarro]], a Filipino singer of Tausūg and Sama descent, performing at the US-Philippine Expo in [[Pomona, California]].]]
* [[Nina Rasul|Santanina T. Rasul]], first [[Moro people|Filipino Muslim]] woman [[Senate of the Philippines|senator]].
* [[Muedzul Lail Tan Kiram]], legitimate Sultan of Sulu Filipino 
* [[Nur Misuari]], former Filipino governor and founder of the [[Moro National Liberation Front]].
* [[Jamalul Kiram III]], self-proclaimed Filipino sultan.
* [[Ismael Kiram II]], self-proclaimed Filipino sultan.
* [[Mat Salleh Rebellion|Mat Salleh]] (Datu Muhammad Salleh), Sabah warrior from [[Inanam]] during the British administration of [[North Borneo]].
* [[Tun Datu Mustapha]] (Tun Datu Mustapha bin Datu Harun), first [[Yang di-Pertua Negeri of Sabah|Yang di-Pertua Negeri]] (Governor) of Sabah and third [[List of Chief Ministers of Sabah|Chief Minister]] of [[Sabah]].
* [[Juhar Mahiruddin]], tenth Yang di-Pertua Negeri (Governor) of Sabah (also partial [[Kadazan-Dusun]] ethnic ancestry).
* [[Musa Aman]], fourteenth Chief Minister of Sabah.
* [[Shafie Apdal]], fifteenth Chief Minister of Sabah.
* [[Sitti]], Filipino singer.
* [[Maria Lourdes Sereno]], 24th Chief Justice of the [[Supreme Court of the Philippines]].
* [[Wawa Zainal Abidin]], Malaysian actress.
* [[Yong Muhajil]], teen housemate in Pinoy Big Brother: Lucky 7.

